obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (49808)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Levy of duty where standard rate and preferential rate are specified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49808&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in respect of`
  line `any article a preferential rate of revenue duty is specified in the First Schedule, or is admissible by virtue`
  line `of a notification under Section 25 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), the duty to be levied and`
  line `collected shall be at the standard rate, unless the owner of the article claims at the time of importation that`
  line `it is chargeable with a preferential rate of duty, being ^1[the produce or manufacture of such preferential`
  line `area] as is notified under sub-section (3) and the article is determined, in accordance with the rules made`
  line `under sub-section (2), to be such produce or manufacture.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for determining`
  line `if any article is ^2[the produce or manufacture of any preferential areas].`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section and the First Schedule, ^3[preferential area] means any country or`
  line `territory which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be such area.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where the Central Government is satisfied`
  line `that, in the interests of trade including promotion of exports, it is necessary to take immediate action for`
  line `discontinuing the preferential rate, or increasing the preferential rate to a rate not exceeding the standard`
  line `rate, or decreasing the preferential rate, in respect of an article specified in the First Schedule, the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct an amendment of the said Schedule to be`
  line `made so as to provide for such discontinuance of, or increase or decrease, as the case may be, in the`
  line `preferential rate.`
  line
  line `(5) Every notification issued under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) shall, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is issued, be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1978, s. 2, for "the produce or manufacture of the United Kingdom or of such other preferential area"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-9-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid ., for "the produce or manufacture of the United Kingdom or of any other preferential area"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-9-1978).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid ., for "United Kingdom" means the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland and "other`
  line `preferential area" (w.e.f. 1-9-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (49809)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Levy of a lower rate of duty under a trade agreement`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49809&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whereunder a trade agreement`
  line `between the Government of India and the Government of a foreign country or territory, duty at a rate`
  line `lower than that specified in the First Schedule is to be charged on articles which are the produce or`
  line `manufacture of such foreign country or territory, the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make rules for determining if any article is the produce or manufacture of such foreign`
  line `country or territory and for requiring the owner to make a claim at the time of importation, supported by`
  line `such evidence as may be prescribed in the said rules, for assessment at the appropriate lower rate under`
  line `such agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises whether any trade agreement applies to any country or territory, or whether`
  line `it has ceased to apply to India or any foreign country or territory, it shall be referred to the Central`
  line `Government for decision and the decision of the Central Government shall be final and shall not be liable`
  line `to be questioned in any court of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (49810)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power of Central Government to levy protective duties in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49810&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `Central Government, upon a recommendation made to it in this behalf by the Tariff Commission`
  line `established under the Tariff Commission Act, 1951 (50 of 1951), is satisfied that circumstances exist`
  line `which render it necessary to take immediate action to provide for the protection of the interests of any`
  line `industry established in India, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, impose`
  line `on any goods imported into India in respect of which the said recommendation is made, a duty of customs`
  line `of such amount, not exceeding the amount proposed in the said recommendation, as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Every duty imposed on any goods under sub-section (1) shall, for the purposes of this Act, be`
  line `deemed to have been specified in the First Schedule as the duty leviable in respect of such goods.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a notification has been issued under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall, unless`
  line `the notification is in the meantime rescinded, have a Bill introduced in Parliament, as soon as may be, but`
  line `in any case during the next session of Parliament following the date of the issue of the notification to give`
  line `effect to the proposals in regard to the continuance of a protective duty of customs on the goods to which`
  line `the notification relates, and the notification shall cease to have effect when such Bill becomes law,`
  line `whether with or without modifications, but without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the notification under sub-section (1) is issued when Parliament is in session, such a`
  line `Bill shall be introduced in Parliament during that session:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where, for any reason, a Bill as aforesaid does not become law within six`
  line `months from the date of its introduction in Parliament, the notification shall cease to have effect on the`
  line `expiration of the said period of six months, but without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (49811)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Duration of protective duties and power of Central Government to alter them`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1978, s. 3, for column (6) (w.e.f. 1-9-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49811&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the`
  line `duty specified in respect of any article in the First Schedule is characterised as protective in ^1[Column (5)] of that Schedule, that duty shall have effect only up to and inclusive of the date, if any,`
  line `specified in that Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in respect of any such article the Central Government is satisfied after such inquiry as it`
  line `thinks necessary that such duty has become ineffective or excessive for the purpose of securing the`
  line `protection intended to be afforded by it to a similar article manufactured in India and that circumstances`
  line `exist which render it necessary to take immediate action, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `increase or reduce such duty to such extent as it thinks necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) Every notification under sub-section (2), insofar as it relates to increase of such duty, shall be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament if it is sitting as soon as may be after the issue of the notification, and if`
  line `it is not sitting within seven days of its re-assembly, and the Central Government shall seek the approval`
  line `of Parliament to the notification by a resolution moved within a period of fifteen days beginning with the`
  line `day on which the notification is so laid before the House of the People and if Parliament makes any`
  line `modification in the notification or directs that the notification should cease to have effect, the notification`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, but without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done thereunder.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any notification issued under sub-section (2),`
  line `including any such notification approved or modified under sub-section (3), may be rescinded by the`
  line `Central Government at any time by notification in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (49812)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Emergency power to Central Government to increase or levy export duties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49812&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in`
  line `respect of any article, whether included in the Second Schedule or not, the Central Government is`
  line `satisfied that the export duty leviable thereon should be increased or that an export duty should be levied,`
  line `and that circumstances exist which render it necessary to take immediate action, the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct an amendment of the Second Schedule to be made so`
  line `as to provide for an increase in the export duty leviable or, as the case may be, for the levy of an export`
  line `duty, on that article.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4) of Section 7 shall apply to any notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1) as they apply in relation to any notification increasing duty issued under`
  line `sub-section (2) of Section 7.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (49813)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 10
  title `Emergency power of Central Government to increase import duties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 110 (w.e.f. 14-5-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49813&sectionno=8A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Emergency power of Central Government to increase import duties.--(1) Where in respect`
  line `of any article included in the First Schedule, the Central Government is satisfied that the import duty`
  line `leviable thereon under section 12 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) should be increased and that circumstances exist which render it necessary to take immediate action, it may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, direct an amendment of that Schedule to be made so as to provide for an increase in the`
  line `import duty leviable on such article to such extent as it thinks necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government shall not issue any notification under this subsection for`
  line `substituting the rate of import duty in respect of any article as specified by an earlier notification issued`
  line `under this sub-section by that Government before such earlier notification has been approved with or`
  line `without modifications under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4) of section 7 shall apply to any notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1) as they apply in relation to any notification increasing duty issued under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 7.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b:
  sectionId (49814)
  sectionNo 8B
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of Central Government to apply safefuard measures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49814&sectionno=8B&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content:
  string
  line `^1 [8B. Power of Central Government to apply safefuard measures.--(1) If the Central Government,`
  line `after conducting such enquiry as it deems fit, is satisfied that any article is imported into India in such`
  line `increased quantity and under such conditions so as to cause or threaten to cause serious injury to domestic`
  line `industry, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, apply such safeguard measures on that article, as`
  line `it deems appropriate.`
  line
  line `(2) The safeguard measures referred to in sub-section (1) shall include imposition of safeguard duty,`
  line `application of tariff-rate quota or such other measure, as the Central Government may consider`
  line `appropriate, to curb the increased quantity of imports of an article to prevent serious injury to domestic`
  line `industry:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such measure shall be applied on an article originating from a developing country so`
  line `long as the share of imports of that article from that country does not exceed three per cent. or where the`
  line `article is originating from more than one developing country, then, so long as the aggregate of the imports`
  line `from each of such developing countries with less than three per cent. import share taken together, does`
  line `not exceed nine per cent. of the total imports of that article into India:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt`
  line `such quantity of any article as it may specify in the notification, when imported from any country or`
  line `territory into India, from payment of the whole or part of the safeguard duty leviable thereon.`
  line
  line `(3) Where tariff-rate quota is used as a safeguard measure, the Central Government shall not fix such`
  line `quota lower than the average level of imports in the last three representative years for which statistics are`
  line `available, unless a different level is deemed necessary to prevent or remedy serious injury.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may allocate such tariff-rate quota to supplying countries having a`
  line `substantial interest in supplying the article concerned, in such manner as may be provided by rules.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, pending the determination under sub-section (1), apply provisional`
  line `safeguard measures under this sub-section on the basis of a preliminary determination that increased`
  line `imports have caused or threatened to cause serious injury to a domestic industry:`
  line
  line `Provided that where, on final determination, the Central Government is of the opinion that increased`
  line `imports have not caused or threatened to cause serious injury to a domestic industry, it shall refund the`
  line `safeguard duty so collected:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any provisional safeguard measure shall not remain in force for more than two`
  line `hundred days from the date on which it was applied.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing sub-sections, a notification issued under subsection (1) or any safeguard measures applied under sub-sections (2), (3), (4) and (5), shall not apply to`
  line `articles imported by a hundred per cent. export-oriented undertaking or a unit in a special economic zone,`
  line unless--
  line
  line `(i) it is specifically made applicable in such notification or to such undertaking or ^2[unit; or]`
  line
  line `(ii) such article is either cleared as such into the domestic tariff area or used in the manufacture of`
  line `any goods that are cleared into the domestic tariff area, in which case, safeguard measures shall be`
  line `applied on the portion of the article so cleared or used, as was applicable when it was imported into`
  line India.
  line
  line `^3[Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section,-`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "hundred per cent. export-oriented undertaking" shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in clause (i) of Explanation 2 to sub-section (1) of section 3 of the`
  line `Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944);`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "special economic zone" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in`
  line `clause (za) of section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005).]`
  line
  line `(7) The safeguard duty imposed under this section shall be in addition to any other duty imposed`
  line `under this Act or under any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(8) The safeguard measures applied under this section shall, unless revoked earlier, cease to have`
  line `effect on the expiry of four years from the date of such application:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government is of the opinion that the domestic industry has taken`
  line `measures to adjust to such injury or threat thereof and it is necessary that the safeguard measures should`
  line `continue to be applied, it may extend the period of such application:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in no case the safeguard measures shall continue to be applied beyond a period`
  line `of ten years from the date on which such measures were first applied.`
  line
  line `(9) The provisions of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) and the rules and regulations made`
  line `thereunder, including those relating to the date for determination of rate of duty, assessment, non-levy,`
  line `short-levy, refunds, interest, appeals, offences and penalties shall, as far as may be, apply to the duty`
  line `chargeable under this section as they apply in relation to duties leviable under that Act.`
  line
  line `(10) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for the`
  line `purposes of this section, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(i) the manner in which articles liable for safeguard measures may be identified;`
  line
  line `(ii) the manner in which the causes of serious injury or causes of threat of serious injury in`
  line `relation to identified article may be determined;`
  line
  line `(iii) the manner of assessment and collection of safeguard duty;`
  line
  line `(iv) the manner in which tariff-rate quota on identified article may be allocated among supplying`
  line countries;
  line
  line `(v) the manner of implementing tariff-rate quota as a safeguard measure;`
  line
  line `(vi) any other safeguard measure and the manner of its application.`
  line
  line `(11) For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "developing country" means a country notified by the Central Government in the Official`
  line Gazette;
  line
  line `(b) "domestic industry" means the producers--`
  line
  line `(i) as a whole of the like article or a directly competitive article in India; or`
  line
  line `(ii) whose collective output of the like article or a directly competitive article in India`
  line `constitutes a major share of the total production of the said article in India;`
  line
  line `(c) "serious injury " means an injury causing significant overall impairment in the position of a`
  line `domestic industry;`
  line
  line `(d) "threat of serious injury " means a clear and imminent danger of serious injury.`
  line
  line `(12) Every notification issued under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the notification or both Houses agree that the notification should not be issued, the`
  line `notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_footnotes:
