obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (49817)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 13
  title `Countervailing duty on subsidized articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49817&sectionno=9&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Countervailing duty on subsidized articles.--(1) Where any country or territory pays, bestows,`
  line `directly or indirectly, any subsidy upon the manufacture or production therein or the exportation`
  line `therefrom of any article including any subsidy on transportation of such article, then, upon the`
  line `importation of any such article into India, whether the same is imported directly from the country of`
  line `manufacture, production or otherwise, and whether it is imported in the same condition as when exported`
  line `from the country of manufacture or production or has been changed in condition by manufacture,`
  line `production or otherwise, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, impose a`
  line `countervailing duty not exceeding the amount of such subsidy.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, a subsidy shall be deemed to exist if--`
  line
  line `(a) there is financial contribution by a Government, or any public body ^2[in the exporting or`
  line `producing country or territory], that is, where--`
  line
  line `(i) a Government practice involves a direct transfer of funds (including grants, loans and`
  line `equity infusion), or potential direct transfer of funds or liabilities, or both;`
  line
  line `(ii) Government revenue that is otherwise due is foregone or not collected (including fiscal`
  line `incentives);`
  line
  line `(iii) a Government provides goods or services other than general infrastructure or purchases`
  line goods;
  line
  line `(iv) a state Government makes payments to a funding mechanism, or entrusts or directs a`
  line `private body to carry out one or more of the type of functions specified in clauses (i) to (iii) above`
  line `which would normally be vested in the Government and the practice in, no real sense, differs`
  line `from practices normally followed by Governments; or`
  line
  line `(b) a Government grants or maintains any form of income or price support, which operates`
  line `directly or indirectly to increase export of any article from, or to reduce import of any article into, its`
  line `territory, and a benefit is thereby conferred.`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) Where the Central Government, on such inquiry as it considers necessary, is of the opinion that`
  line `circumvention of countervailing duty imposed under sub-section (1) has taken place, either by altering the`
  line `description or name or composition of the article on which such duty has been imposed or by import of`
  line `such article in an unassembled or disassembled form or by changing the country of its origin or export or`
  line `in any other manner, whereby the countervailing duty so imposed is rendered ineffective, it may extend`
  line `the countervailing duty to such other article also ^4[ from such date, not earlier than the date of initiation of`
  line `the inquiry, as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify].]`
  line
  line `^5[(1B) Where the Central Government, on such inquiry as it considers necessary, is of the opinion that`
  line `absorption of countervailing duty imposed under sub-section (1) has taken place whereby the`
  line `countervailing duty so imposed is rendered ineffective, it may modify such duty to counter the effect of`
  line `such absorption, from such date, not earlier than the date of initiation of the inquiry, as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this sub-section, "obsorption of countervailing duty" is said to`
  line `have taken place,`
  line
  line `(a) if there is a decrease in the export price of an article without any commensurate change in the`
  line `resale price in India of such article imported from the exporting country or territory; or`
  line
  line `(b) under such other circumstances as may be provided by rules.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, pending the determination in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `section and the rules made thereunder of the amount of subsidy, impose a countervailing duty under this`
  line `sub-section not exceeding the amount of such subsidy as provisionally estimated by it and if such`
  line `countervailing duty exceeds the subsidy as so determined,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government shall, having regard to such determination and as soon as may be`
  line `after such determination, reduce such countervailing duty; and`
  line
  line `(b) refund shall be made of so much of such countervailing duty which has been collected as is in`
  line `excess of the countervailing duty as so reduced.`
  line
  line `^6[(2A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), a notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1) or any countervailing duty imposed under sub-section (2) shall not apply to article`
  line `imported by a hundred per cent. export-oriented undertaking or a unit in a special economic zone,`
  line unless,-
  line
  line `(i) it is specifically made applicable in such notification or to such undertaking or unit; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such articles is either cleared as such into the domestic tariff area or used in the`
  line `manufacture of any goods that are cleared into the domestic tariff area, in which case,`
  line `countervailing duty shall be imposed on that portion of the article so cleared or used, as was`
  line `applicable when it was imported into India.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-For the purposed of this sub-section,-`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "hundred per cent. export-oriented undertaking" shall have the same meaning`
  line `as assigned to it in clause (i) of Explanation 2 to sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Central Excise`
  line `Act, 1944 (1 of 1944);`
  line
  line `(b) the expression special economic zone shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in`
  line `clause (za) of section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005;]`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to any rules made by the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, the`
  line `countervailing duty under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall not be levied unless it is determined`
  line that--
  line
  line `(a) the subsidy relates to export performance;`
  line
  line `(b) the subsidy relates to the use of domestic goods over imported goods in the export article; or`
  line
  line `^7[(c) the subsidy has been conferred on a limited number of persons engaged in the manufacture,`
  line `production or export of articles;]`
  line
  line `(4) If the Central Government, is of the opinion that the injury to the domestic industry which is`
  line `difficult to repair, is caused by massive imports in a relatively short period, of the article benefiting from`
  line `subsidies paid or bestowed and where in order to preclude the recurrence of such injury, it is necessary to`
  line `levy countervailing duty retrospectively, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, levy countervailing duty from a date prior to the date of imposition of countervailing duty under`
  line `sub-section (2) but not beyond ninety days from the date of notification under that sub-section and`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, such duty shall be payable`
  line `from the date as specified in the notification issued under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(5) The countervailing duty chargeable under this section shall be in addition to any other duty`
  line `imposed under this Act or any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(6) The countervailing duty imposed under this section shall, unless revoked earlier, cease to have`
  line `effect on the expiry of five years from the date of such imposition:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government, in a review, is of the opinion that the cessation of such duty`
  line `is likely to lead to continuation or recurrence of subsidization and injury, it may, from time to time,`
  line `extend the period of such imposition for a further period ^8[up to five years] and such further period shall`
  line `commence from the date of order of such extension:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where a review initiated before the expiry of the aforesaid period of five years`
  line `has not come to a conclusion before such expiry, the countervailing duty may continue to remain in force`
  line `pending the outcome of such a review for a further period not exceeding one year.`
  line
  line `^9[Povided also that if the said duty is revoked temporarily, the period of such revocation shall not`
  line `exceed one year at a time.]`
  line
  line `(7) The amount of any such subsidy as referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall, from`
  line `time to time, be ascertained and determined by the Central Government, after such inquiry as it may`
  line `consider necessary and the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules`
  line `for the identification of such article and for the assessment and collection of any countervailing duty`
  line `imposed upon the importation thereof under this section.`
  line
  line `^10[(7A) The provisions of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) and the rules and regulations made`
  line `thereunder, including those relating to the date for determination of rate of duty, assessment, non-levy,`
  line `short levy, refunds, interest, appeals, offences and penalties shall, as far as may be, apply to the duty`
  line `chargeable under this section as they apply in relation to duties leviable under that Act.]`
  line
  line `(8) Every notification issued under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is issued, be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1995, s. 2, for sections 9, 9A and 9B (w.e.f. 1-1-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 61, for within the territory of the exporting or producing country (w.e.f. 18-4-2006).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 102 (w.e.f. 28-03-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 102 (w.e.f. 28-03-2021).`
  line
  line `6Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 102 (w.e.f. 28-03-2021).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 109, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 31-3-2017).`
  line
  line `8.Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 102, for of five years (w.e.f. 28-03-2021).`
  line
  line `9.Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 102 (w.e.f. 28-03-2021).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 99, for sub-section (7A) (w.e.f. 1-1-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (49818)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 14
  title `Anti-dumping duty on dumped articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49818&sectionno=9A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Anti-dumping duty on dumped articles.--(1) Where ^2[any article is exported by an exporter or`
  line `producer] from any country or territory (hereinafter in this section referred to as the exporting country or`
  line `territory) to India at less than its normal value, then, upon the importation of such article into India, the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, impose an anti-dumping duty not`
  line `exceeding the margin of dumping in relation to such article.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) margin of dumping, in relation to an article, means the difference between its export price`
  line `and its normal value;`
  line
  line `(b) export price, in relation to an article, means the price of the article exported from the`
  line `exporting country or territory and in cases where there is no export price or where the export price is`
  line `unreliable because of association or a compensatory arrangement between the exporter and the`
  line `importer or a third party, the export price may be constructed on the basis of the price at which the`
  line `imported articles are first resold to an independent buyer or if the article is not resold to an`
  line `independent buyer, or not resold in the condition as imported, on such reasonable basis as may be`
  line `determined in accordance with the rules made under sub-section (6);`
  line
  line `(c) normal value, in relation to an article, means--`
  line
  line `(i) the comparable price, in the ordinary course of trade, for the like article when ^3[destined`
  line `for consumption] in the exporting country or territory as determined in accordance with the rules`
  line `made under sub-section (6); or`
  line
  line `(ii) when there are no sales of the like article in the ordinary course of trade in the domestic`
  line `market of the exporting country or territory, or when because of the particular market situation or`
  line `low volume of the sales in the domestic market of the exporting country or territory, such sales do`
  line `not permit a proper comparison, the normal value shall be either--`
  line
  line `(a) comparable representative price of the like article when exported from the exporting`
  line `country or ^4[territory to] an appropriate third country as determined in accordance with the rules`
  line `made under sub-section (6); or`
  line
  line `(b) the cost of production of the said article in the country of origin along with reasonable`
  line `addition for administrative, selling and general costs, and for profits, as determined in accordance`
  line `with the rules made under sub-section (6):`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of import of the article from a country other than the country of origin`
  line `and where the article has been merely transhipped through the country of export or such article is not`
  line `produced in the country of export or there is no comparable price in the country of export, the normal`
  line `value shall be determined with reference to its price in the country of origin.`
  line
  line `^5[(1A) Where the Central Government, on such inquiry as it may consider necessary, is of the opinion`
  line `that circumvention of anti-dumping duty imposed under sub-section (1) has taken place, either by altering`
  line `the description or name or composition of the article subject to such anti-dumping duty or by import of`
  line `such article in an unassembled or disassembled form or by changing the country of its origin or export or`
  line `in any other manner, whereby the antidumping duty so imposed is rendered ineffective, it may extend the anti-dumping duty to such article or an article originating in or exported from such country, as the case`
  line `may be ^6[from such date, not earlier than the date of initiation of the inquiry, as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify].]`
  line
  line `^7[(1B) Where the Central Government, on such inquiry as it may consider necessary, is of the opinion`
  line `that absorption of anti-dumping duty imposed under sub-section (1) has taken place whereby the antidumping duty so imposed is rendered ineffective, it may modify such duty to counter the effect of such`
  line `absorption, from such date, not earlier than the date of intitiation of the inquiry, as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-For the purposes of this sub-section, "absorption of anti-dumping duty" is said to have`
  line `taken place,`
  line
  line `(a) if there is a decrease in the export price of an article without any commensurate change in the`
  line `cost of production of such article or export price of such article to countries other than India or resale`
  line `price in India of such article imported from the exporting country or territory; or`
  line
  line `(b) under such other circumstances as may be provided by rules.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, pending the determination in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `section and the rules made thereunder of the normal value and the margin of dumping in relation to any`
  line `article, impose on the importation of such article into India an anti-dumping duty on the basis of a`
  line `provisional estimate of such value and margin and if such anti-dumping duty exceeds the margin as so`
  line `determined:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government shall, having regard to such determination and as soon as may be`
  line `after such determination, reduce such anti-dumping duty; and`
  line
  line `(b) refund shall be made of so much of the anti-dumping duty which has been collected as is in`
  line `excess of the anti-dumping duty as so reduced.`
  line
  line `^8[(2A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) and sub-section (2), a notification`
  line `issued under sub-section (1) or any anti-dumping duty imposed under sub-section (2) shall not apply to`
  line `articles imported by a hundred per cent. export-oriented undertaking or a unit in a special economic zone,`
  line unless,
  line
  line `(i) it is specifically made applicable in such notification or to such undertaking or unit; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such article is either cleared as such into the domestic tariff area or used in the manufacture of`
  line `any goods that are cleared into the domestic tariff area, in which case, anti-dumping duty shall be`
  line `imposed on that portion of the article so cleared or used, as was applicable when it was imported into`
  line India.
  line
  line `Explanation.-For the purposes of this section,-`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "hundred per cent. export-oriented undertaking" shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in clause (i) of Explanation 2 to sub-section (1) of section 3 of the`
  line `Central Exise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944);`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "special economic zone" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in`
  line `clause (za) of section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005).]`
  line
  line `(3) If the Central Government, in respect of the dumped article under inquiry, is of the opinion that--`
  line
  line `(i) there is a history of dumping which caused injury or that the importer was, or should have`
  line `been, aware that the exporter practices dumping and that such dumping would cause injury; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the injury is caused by massive dumping of an article imported in a relatively short time`
  line `which in the light of the timing and the volume of imported article dumped and other circumstances is`
  line `likely to seriously undermine the remedial effect of the antidumping duty liable to be levied,`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, levy anti-dumping duty`
  line `retrospectively from a date prior to the date of imposition of anti-dumping duty under sub-section (2) but`
  line `not beyond ninety days from the date of notification under that sub-section, and notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any law for the time being in force, such duty shall be payable at such rate and from such`
  line `date as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(4) The anti-dumping duty chargeable under this section shall be in addition to any other duty`
  line `imposed under this Act or any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(5) The anti-dumping duty imposed under this section shall, unless revoked earlier, cease to have`
  line `effect on the expiry of five years from the date of such imposition:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government, in a review, is of the opinion that the cessation of such duty`
  line `is likely to lead to continuation or recurrence of dumping and injury, it may, from time to time, extend the period of such imposition for a further period ^9[up to five years] and such further period shall commence from`
  line `the date of order of such extension:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where a review initiated before the expiry of the aforesaid period of five years`
  line `has not come to a conclusion before such expiry, the anti-dumping duty may continue to remain in force`
  line `pending the outcome of such a review for a further period not exceeding one year.`
  line
  line `^10[Provided also that if the said duty is revoked temporarily, the period of such revocation shall not`
  line `exceed one year at a time.]`
  line
  line `(6) The margin of dumping as referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall, from time to`
  line `time, be ascertained and determined by the Central Government, after such inquiry as it may consider`
  line `necessary and the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for the`
  line `purposes of this section, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing, such rules may provide`
  line `for the manner in which articles liable for any anti-dumping duty under this section may be identified, and`
  line `for the manner in which the export price and the normal value of, and the margin of dumping in relation`
  line `to, such articles may be determined and for the assessment and collection of such anti-dumping duty.`
  line
  line `^11[(6A) The margin of dumping in relation to an article, exported by an exporter or producer, under`
  line `inquiry under sub-section (6) shall be determined on the basis of records concerning normal value and`
  line `export price maintained, and information provided, by such exporter or producer:`
  line `Provided that where an exporter or producer fails to provide such records or information, the margin`
  line `of dumping for such exporter or producer shall be determined on the basis of facts available.]`
  line
  line `(7) Every notification issued under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is issued, be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `^12[(8) The provisions of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) and the rules and regulations made`
  line `thereunder, including those relating to the date for determination of rate of duty, assessment, non-levy,`
  line `short levy, refunds, interest, appeals, offences and penalties shall, as far as may be, apply to the duty`
  line `chargeable under this section as they apply in relation to duties leviable under that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1995, s. 2, for sections 9, 9A and 9B (w.e.f. 1-1-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 101, for any article is exported (w.e.f. 19-8-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 62, for meant for consumption (w.e.f. 18-4-2006).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 2003, s. 131, for territory or (w.e.f. 14-5-2003).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 58 (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
  line
  line `6.Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 103 (w.e.f. 28-03-2021).`
  line
  line `7.Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 103 (w.e.f. 28-03-2021).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 103, for sub-section (2A) (w.e.f. 28-03-2021).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 103, for of five years (w.e.f. 28-03-2021).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 103 (w.e.f. 28-03-2021).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 101 (w.e.f. 19-8-2009).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by s. 101, ibid., for sub-section (8) (w.e.f. 1-1-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_aa:
  sectionId (49819)
  sectionNo 9AA
  orderNo 15
  title `Refund of anti-dumping duty in certain cases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_aa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_aa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49819&sectionno=9AA&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_9_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[9AA. Refund of anti-dumping duty in certain cases.--(1) ^2[Where upon determination by an`
  line `officer authorised in this behalf by the Central Government under clause (ii) of sub-section (2), an`
  line `importer proves to the satisfaction of the Central Government that he has paid anti-dumping duty imposed`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 9A on any article, in excess of the actual margin of dumping in relation to`
  line `such article, the Central Government shall, as soon as may be, reduce such anti-dumping duty as is in`
  line `excess of actual margin of dumping so determined, in relation to such article or such importer, and such`
  line `importer shall be entitled to refund of such excess duty]:`
  line
  line `Provided that such importer shall not be entitled to refund of so much of such excess duty under this`
  line `sub-section which is refundable under sub-section (2) of section 9A.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--for the purposes of this sub-section, the expressions, "margin of dumping", "export`
  line `price" and "normal value" shall have the same meaning respectively assigned to them in the Explanation`
  line `to sub-section (1) of section 9A.`
  line
  line `(2) the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to--`
  line
  line `(i) provide for the manner in which and the time within which the importer may make application`
  line `for the purposes of sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(ii) authorise the officer of the Central Government who shall dispose of such application on`
  line `behalf of the Central Government within the time specified in such rules; and`
  line
  line `(iii) provide the manner in which the excess duty referred to in sub-section (1) shall be--`
  line
  line `(A) determined by the officer referred to in clause (ii); and`
  line
  line `(B) refunded by the Deputy Commissioner of Customs or Assistant Commissioner of`
  line `Customs, as the case may be, after such determination].]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_aa_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 89 (w.e.f. 12-5-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 59, for certain words (w.e.f. 8-4-2011).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_b:
  sectionId (49820)
  sectionNo 9B
  orderNo 16
  title `NO levy under section 9 or section 9A in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 89 (w.e.f. 12-5-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49820&sectionno=9B&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[9B. No levy under section 9 or section 9A in certain cases.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 9 or section 9A,--`
  line
  line `(a) no article shall be subjected to both countervailing duty and anti-dumping duty to compensate`
  line `for the same situation of dumping or export subsidization;`
  line
  line `(b) the Central Government shall not levy any countervailing duty or antidumping duty--`
  line
  line `(i) under section 9 or section 9A by reasons of exemption of such articles from duties or taxes`
  line `borne by the like article when meant for consumption in the country of origin or exportation or by`
  line `reasons of refund of such duties or taxes;`
  line
  line `(ii) under sub-section (1) of each of these sections, on the import into India of any article`
  line `from a member country of the World Trade Organisation or from a country with whom`
  line `Government of India has a most favoured nation agreement (hereinafter referred as a specified`
  line `country), unless in accordance with the rules made under sub-section (2) of this section, a`
  line `determination has been made that import of such article into India causes or threatens material`
  line `injury to any established industry in India or materially retards the establishment of any industry`
  line `in India; and`
  line
  line `(iii) under sub-section (2) of each of these sections, on import into India of any article from`
  line `the specified countries unless in accordance with the rules made under sub-section (2) of this`
  line `section, a preliminary findings has been made of subsidy or dumping and consequent injury to`
  line `domestic industry; and a further determination has also been made that a duty is necessary to`
  line `prevent injury being caused during the investigation:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in sub-clauses (ii) and (iii) of clause (b) shall apply if a`
  line `countervailing duty or an anti-dumping duty has been imposed on any article to prevent injury or`
  line `threat of an injury to the domestic industry of a third country exporting the like articles to India;`
  line
  line `(c) the Central Government may not levy--`
  line
  line `(i) any countervailing duty under section 9, at any time, upon receipt of satisfactory voluntary`
  line `undertakings from the Government of the exporting country or territory agreeing to eliminate or`
  line `limit the subsidy or take other measures concerning its effect, or the exporter agreeing to revise`
  line `the price of the article and if the Central Government is satisfied that the injurious effect of the`
  line `subsidy is eliminated thereby;`
  line
  line `(ii) any anti-dumping duty under section 9A, at any time, upon receipt of satisfactory`
  line `voluntary undertaking from any exporter to revise its prices or to cease exports to the area in`
  line `question at dumped price and if the Central Government is satisfied that the injurious effect of`
  line `dumping is eliminated by such action.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for the purposes`
  line `of this section, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing, such rules may provide for the manner in which any investigation may be made for the purposes of this section, the factors to which`
  line `regard shall be at in any such investigation and for all matters connected with such investigation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_c:
  sectionId (49821)
  sectionNo 9C
  orderNo 17
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49821&sectionno=9C&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_9_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[9C. Appeal.--^2[(1) An appeal against the order of determination or review thereof shall lie to the`
  line `Customs, Excise and Service Tax Appellate Tribunal constituted under section 129 of the Customs Act,`
  line `1962 (52 of 1962) (hereinafter referred to as the Appellate Tribunal), in respect of the existence, degree`
  line `and effect of--`
  line
  line `(i) any subsidy or dumping in relation to import of any article; or`
  line
  line `(ii) import of any article into India in such increased quantities and under such condition so as to`
  line `cause or threatening to cause serious injury to domestic industry requiring imposition of safeguard`
  line `duty in relation to import of that article.]`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) An appeal under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by a fee of fifteen thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(1B) Every application made before the Appellate Tribunal,--`
  line
  line `(a) in an appeal under sub-section (1), for grant of stay or for rectification of mistake or for`
  line `any other purpose; or`
  line
  line `(b) for restoration of an appeal or an application,`
  line
  line `shall be accompanied by a fee of five hundred rupees.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under this section shall be filed within ninety days of the date of order under`
  line `appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain any appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `ninety days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in`
  line time.
  line
  line `(3) The AppellateTribunal may, after giving the parties to the appeal, an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming, modifying or annulling the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-sections (1), (2), (5) and (6) of section 129C of the Customs Act, 1962`
  line `(52 of 1962) shall apply to the Appellate Tribunal in the discharge of its functions under this Act as they`
  line `apply to it in the discharge of its functions under the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962).`
  line
  line `(5) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be heard by a Special Bench constituted by the President`
  line `of the Appellate Tribunal for hearing such appeals and such Bench shall consist of the President and not`
  line `less than two members and shall include one judicial member and one technical member.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 89 (w.e.f. 12-5-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 87, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-11-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (49822)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 18
  title `Rules to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49822&sectionno=10&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the`
  line `rule shall, thereafter, have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (49823)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of Central Government to alter duties under certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49823&sectionno=11&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary so to do for the purpose of giving effect to any`
  line `agreement entered into before the commencement of this Act with a foreign Government, it may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, increase or reduce the duties referred to in section 2 to such extent as`
  line `each case may require:`
  line
  line `Provided that no notification under this sub-section increasing or reducing the duties as aforesaid`
  line `shall be issued by the Central Government after the expiration of a period of one year from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall, as soon as may be after it is issued, be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (49824)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 20
  title `Power of Central Government to amend First Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2003, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49824&sectionno=11A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Power of Central Government to amend First Schedule.--(1) Where the Central`
  line `Government is satisfied that it is necessary so to do in the public interest, it may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, amend the First Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that such amendment shall not alter or affect in any manner the rates specified in that`
  line `Schedule in respect of goods at which duties of customs shall be leviable on the goods under the Customs`
  line `Act, 1962 (52 of 1962).`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the notification or both Houses agree that the notification should not be issued, the`
  line `notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (49825)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 21
  title `Repeal and saving`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359&sectionId=49825&sectionno=12&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_197551_1554713855359
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Indian Tariff Act, 1934 (32 of 1934), and the Indian Tariff`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1949 (1 of 1949), are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of any of the Acts mentioned in sub-section (1), anything done or any`
  line `action taken (including any notification published and any rules and orders made or deemed to have been`
  line `made under the provisions of those Acts and in force immediately before the commencement of this Act)`
  line `shall, insofar as such thing or action is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have`
  line `been done or taken under the provisions of this Act and shall continue in force accordingly until`
  line `superseded by anything done or any action taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (49826)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 22
  title `Consequential amendment of Act 52 of 1962.`
